  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6813 sitting 47 points below the 6860 flip and well under the massive 6900 gamma wall, dealers are in full stabilizing mode and likely buying this dip aggressively as they're long gamma. The PIN regime with 32.7B in total GEX creates strong mean-reversion forces, suggesting any further weakness toward the 6755 negative gamma pocket will trigger accelerated dealer buying. Key resistance comes at 6850-6875 (3.8B-3.2B walls) and especially 6900 (5.4B), where dealers will sell rallies hard.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce back toward 6850-6875 with strong support here.",
